I moved 'the Vitests' to this directory, to stop Vitest evaluating Storybook tests without Storybook libraries loaded.  Otherwise it makes loads of warnings that are not constructive but will block automation.

The following test files are actually using the network so must be "on Wifi" and browser thread features 
* InstallWorker uses threads/ Workers
* MessageDistribution uses threads/ Workers
* NetworkedListService uses LocalStorsge and RemoteStorage    IOIO
* cURL use HTTPS and TCP, not any browser features
* RemoteStorage uses TCP and HTTPS to send messages to the API 


* DataCache needs updating so can be run from Node            IOIO
* SharedStateWorker CAN NBE UNIT TESTED if deps are supplied
* TestList can be run from Node as it uses MockLocalStorage and fixtures
